I often think about the men and women we met on this tour to Kuwait/Iraq.. and I wonder where they are, how they are now, and if some of them even made it back. These tours (but this one in particular) left such a mark on my heart that I don’t think will ever fade. I don’t know if I’ll ever think about certain things the same anymore but I know one thing for sure - Our US military is F ing BADASS. Their bravery, skill and dedication is unmatched. You don’t know how real it is until you see it face to face. And we saw it face to face that week. 🇺🇸

So Happy Memorial Day! Forever grateful for  the brave men and women who fought for us, and forever proud to be an American. 

#memorialday #memorialdayweekend #proudamerican #americangirl #grateful #USA #USO #dcc #usotour #dallascowboyscheerleaders #showgroup

Camps are a staple of summertime in Texas. They help the kids get some energy out and have fun outside of the house for a couple hours, but this camp in particular was so special. I loved seeing their love and excitement for riding and horses develop over the 5 days this week. From being super hesitant on day 1, to asking if we can get there early by day 4 and 5, it was truly a transformation. They didn’t care if they were hot, dirty or exhausted. They couldn’t wait to go back. 🥰Thank you @tvrtexas for a week these kids will remember for a long time - until next year!! 💯🙌🏼🐎
